<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,900,1320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kitakami" authorityName="Kitakami" box="[780,1124,1152,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Philorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis box="[780,1013,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Philorus longirostris</emphasis>
Kitakami
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1192,1259,1153,1176]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Japan</collectingCountry>
, but can be easily separated from it by the distal margin of both lobes of the cercus in middle being slightly concave and the fused finger-like gonocoxite being long, apically with some long stout black bristles. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1318,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Philorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis box="[1083,1318,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Philorus longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the distal margins of both lobes of the cercus in middle are not concave, the fused gonocoxite are short and not finger-like and the inner gonocoxal is long and slender (
<bibRefCitation author="Kitakami" box="[653,833,1296,1320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refString="Kitakami, S. (1931) The Blephariceridae of Japan. Memoirs of the College of Sciences, Kyoto Imperial University, 6, 53 - 108." type="journal article" year="1931">
Kitakami, 
<number box="[773,833,1296,1320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1931.0">1931</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
